</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-fe1b" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-21_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-22_ pf-text-1">The EWC was established in April 2015, succeeding the General Teaching Council for Wales (GTCW).


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1">The council registers over 80,000 educational professionals, including teachers, support staff, and further education lecturers.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1">EWC’s Code of Professional Conduct and Practice sets out the standards expected of registered practitioners, ensuring they maintain public trust and confidence.










 














</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1">In recent years, the EWC has conducted over 100 fitness-to-practise hearings annually, reinforcing the importance of professional accountability.











 














</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-30_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-31_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-32_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-34_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Education Workforce Council (EWC)</strong> - A regulatory body responsible for maintaining a register of education practitioners, setting professional standards, and ensuring adherence to these standards.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Fitness-to-practise</strong> - A process to determine whether an educational professional can continue in their role, considering their conduct, competence, and health.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Code of professional conduct and practice</strong> - A document outlining the professional standards and behaviours expected from registered education practitioners.


</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-41_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-42_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-43_ pf-heading-1-h3">The Importance of the EWC
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-45_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The EWC’s role extends beyond mere registration. It is crucial for upholding professional standards, providing guidance, and ensuring practitioners are fit to practise. This regulatory framework is essential for several reasons:























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-47_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-48_ pf-text-1"><strong>Maintaining quality</strong> - By setting and enforcing professional standards, the EWC ensures that educational practitioners provide high-quality education.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-50_ pf-text-1"><strong>Protecting students</strong> - Fitness-to-practise hearings and the Code of Conduct protect students from unfit practitioners, ensuring a safe and conducive learning environment.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-52_ pf-text-1"><strong>Professional development </strong>- The EWC promotes continuous professional development, ensuring educators stay current with the latest educational practices and methodologies.











</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-54_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-55_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-56_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommended best practices for compliance
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-58_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-59_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular training and updates</strong> - Educational institutions should ensure their staff undergo regular training to stay updated with the latest EWC guidelines and educational best practices.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-61_ pf-text-1"><strong>Robust recruitment processes</strong> - Schools and colleges should implement thorough recruitment processes to verify potential employees' registration and fitness-to-practise status.












</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-63_ pf-text-1"><strong>Compliance monitoring</strong> - Institutions should have systems to monitor compliance with EWC standards, including regular internal audits and adherence checks.













</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-65_ pf-text-1"><strong>Support for professional development</strong> - Providing opportunities for continuous professional development can help practitioners meet EWC’s standards and enhance their skills.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-67_ pf-text-1"><strong>Effective record-keeping </strong>- Accurate records of professional development activities, compliance checks, and disciplinary actions are crucial for transparency and accountability.














</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-69_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-70_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-71_ pf-heading-1-h3">Legislation and regulations
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-73_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The EWC operates under several legislative frameworks, including:


























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-75_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-76_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Education (Wales) Act 2014</strong> - Established the EWC and outlined its functions and responsibilities.
